The paper discusses the use of linear transformations in deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The focus on improving information flow and easing training suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of convolutional layers and skip-connections suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The mention of gradient vanishing problems and feature reuse suggests that the paper may also be relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) and data structures (cs.DS).
